{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σίδηρος</b> [ῐ], <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>σίδᾱρος</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 42(1).102.61 (Epid., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], etc.: ; also ἡ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Theriaca” 923 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>neuter</i> <b>σίδηρον</b>, τό, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Scholia D 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.151, variant in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.65 and 3rd c.BC: Daimachus Historicus 4J. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] (but probably <i>falsa lectio</i> for{σιδήριον} in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 19.72, compare 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see at {Ἀκίς}): _plural_ σίδηρα 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 2.12, “Etymologicum Magnum” 26.36, 12th c.AD: Tzetzes, Joannes Grammaticus (see. below)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: —<b>iron</b>, σ. πολιός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.366, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.168; ἰόεις 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.850; μέλας 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 151; αἴθων 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.485, +others; πολύκμητος 6.48, +others, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.393 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; as an article of traffic, οἰνίζοντο.. Ἀχαιοί, ἄλλοι μὲν χαλκῷ, ἄλλοι δ᾽ αἴθωνι σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.473; πλέων.. μετὰ χαλκόν· ἄγω δ᾽ αἴθωνα σίδηρον 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.184 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χαλκός τε χρυσός τε πολύκμητός τε σ., of treasures, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.133, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; as a prize, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 23.261, 850 \">Refs</a>]; Σκύθης σ., because brought from the Euxine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 818; ὁ πόντιος ξεῖνος.. θηκτὸς σ. [prev. work] 942 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> frequently as a symbol of <b>hardness</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare (σιδήρεος 1.2)\">Refs</a>], or of <b>stubborn force</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.372, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.494 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὀφθαλμοὶ ὡσεὶ κέρα ἕστασαν ἠὲ σ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\". [prev. work] 211; οὔ σφι λίθος χρὼς οὐδὲ σ. 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.510; ἐκ σ. κεχάλκευται.. καρδίαν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 123.4, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 658; ἦσθα πέτρος ἢ σ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1279 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 666c \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also of <b>firmness, steadfastness</b>, πέτρης ὅ γ᾽ ἔχων νόον ἠὲ σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Moschus Bucolicus 4.44, compare 3rd c.AD(?): Achilles Tatius Astronomus 5.22. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>anything made of iron, iron tool</b> or <b>implement</b>, for husbandry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.485, compare 23.834 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: also of weapons, <b>arrow-head</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.123 \">Refs</a>]; <b>sword</b> or <b>knife</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 18.34, 23.30; αὐτὸς γὰρ ἐφέλκεται ἄνδρα σ. 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.294, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 966 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>axe-head</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.587 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>arms</b>, οἱ Ἀθηναῖοι σ. κατέθεντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.6; ὅπλοις τε καὶ σιδήρῳ διώξειν “OGI” 532.25 (Galatia, 1st c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also, <b>knife, sickle</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 387 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>fishing-hooks</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 21.49 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <b>irons, fetters</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 2.12, 12th c.AD: Tzetzes, Joannes Grammaticus “Historiarum variarum chiliades” 13.302 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; compare σιδήριον. <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>place for selling iron, smithy</b> or <b>cutler's shop</b>, ἀγαγόντα εἰς τὸν σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.3.7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4604","accentedUnicode":"σίδηρος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4603","matchingForm":"σιδήρεος","stepTransliteration":"sidēreos","gloss":"iron","_zh_tw_Gloss":"鐵","_es_Gloss":"hierro","_zh_Gloss":"铁"}],"shortDef":"iron","mediumDef":"<b>iron, (metal) </b> <ref='Rev.18.12'>Rev. 18:12</ref>*","stepGloss":"iron","stepTransliteration":"sidēros","count":1,"_es_Definition":"hierro","_zh_tw_Definition":"鐵 (啟 18:12)","_zh_Definition":"铁 (启 18:12)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sắt","_zh_tw_Gloss":"鐵","_es_Gloss":"hierro","_zh_Gloss":"铁"}]}